  - The block `bb11` is executed after either `bb6` or `bb7`, so its frequency is the sum of the frequencies of those two blocks, but it is executed only once per function call.
  - The block `bb6` is the least hot because it is only executed when the `fcmp ogt` condition is true, which is less frequent than the equality or default path.

- The hottest block, `bb28`, is part of the main loop that processes up to 60,000 elements, making it the most frequently executed block.

- The hottest block is `bb6` because it contains a loop structure, as indicated by the back edge to itself and the presence of the `llvm.loop` metadata. Loops typically execute multiple iterations, making them the most frequently executed blocks.
